{"title":"What should I ask Fareed Zakaria?","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/872133815/0/marginalrevolution~What-should-I-ask-Fareed-Zakaria.html","date":1708848107000,"content":"<p>Here is <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://fareedzakaria.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Fareed’s home page</a>, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fareed_Zakaria\" target=\"_blank\">here is Wikipedia</a>:</p>\r\n<blockquote><p><b>Fareed Rafiq Zakaria…</b>is an <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian-American\">Indian-American</a> journalist, political commentator, and author. He is the host of <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CNN\">CNN</a>‘s <i><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fareed_Zakaria_GPS\">Fareed Zakaria GPS</a></i> and writes a weekly paid column for <i><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Washington_Post\">The Washington Post</a>.</i><sup></sup> He has been a columnist for <i><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Newsweek\">Newsweek</a></i>, editor of <i><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Newsweek_International\">Newsweek International</a></i>, and an <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Editor_at_large\">editor at large</a> of <i><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time_(magazine)\">Time</a>.</i><sup></sup></p></blockquote>\r\n<p>He was managing editor of <em>Foreign Affairs</em> at age 28, briefly a wine columnist for Slate, and much more.  His new book <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.amazon.com/Age-Revolutions-Progress-Backlash-Present/dp/0393239233/ref=sr_1_2?dib=eyJ2IjoiMSJ9.FXULCvHJA2T7iF8s0U6j8qL5G5IoteVWdyulFAnXnwZb7D983KswOCVgrk4V-jpfiTBY4H_XDg_W3zth5w0dYhMSS91PXrVvuiC7RqJBo5IGuyqS-SsYAVym70kbeJLDaEvHq12_e1PWn5v61TyeWRoq7zBfPd3Nkg4EigOrk3e7dr2mgbG6VXqQvHhnB1a131YKNtp8tERkBaEaVWxrpkKYuvgJKUvnrCcm95db05YWQhn6D2eGdbtlkXK8WjExmYjJ3gPQnznWkc9jSzm5T7SwJrvy-WEi3t8vz9s2VyM.nMM-c4iqwTqjB0iIkgS7jdMp-NJM7TaxuqQkvL7v11g&amp;dib_tag=se&amp;keywords=fareed+zakaria&amp;qid=1708783267&amp;sr=8-2\" target=\"_blank\">Age of Revolutions: Progress and Backlash from 1600 to the Present</a> is very classically liberal, and in my terms “Progress Studies”-oriented.</p>\r\n<p>So what should I ask him?</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/02/what-should-i-ask-fareed-zakaria.html\">What should I ask Fareed Zakaria?</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img height=\"1\" width=\"1\" src=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/i/872133815/0/marginalrevolution\" />\r\n<div><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/28/872133815/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/fblike20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/29/872133815/marginalrevolution,\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/pinterest20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/24/872133815/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/x.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/19/872133815/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/email20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/20/872133815/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/rss20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://